the_answers_on_my_fingertips.description:
If anxious families and supporters were able to get just one photograph to prove a person's existence, and to answer five simple questions regarding their basic well being, it would go a long way to helping them during this stressful time.&#13;
&#13;
These questions would be predetermined before a person's capture and answered in binary by a person placing their fingers together or leaving them apart at any opportunity when a picture or video is captured or even when any contact is made and communication is restricted.

camouflage.description:
The main question that has driven my first concept is: &#13;
"How to establish contact with prisoners without using modern technologies and without getting guards / institutions suspicious."&#13;
&#13;
If a single person (e.g a family member) or an institution (e.g. Amnesty International) that might be considered as not having the same interest as the people capturing a prisoner try to establish contact it might be difficult to "get through". &#13;
&#13;
Here are some ideas how to "get through" by using camouflage ... which sometimes means using their own weapons against them.&#13;
